screen_name: This was when I was told in a panic, “You tested positive for COVID-19”. Way to wake me up.
This was when I was told in a panic, “You tested positive for COVID-19”. Way to wake me up.

Day 5: More doctors called and had to report in a lengthy call with the health department. I think my fever is lowering, but my headaches back in full force. No coughing, but my body’s exhausted. I can’t sleep or walk around due to my head pounding. Just kinda laying here.

Day 4 part 3: After I sorted out all my calls for the morning. I realized my symptoms werent half bad. I was only taking a little bit of tylenol and drinking water, but I had no headache and only a minor cough. Fever still persisted but it was going down.

Day 3: Woke up with a massive headache. I don’t usually get headaches, but when I got out of bed this morning I almost couldnt stand up. I felt achy all day, and I drank water all day to combat the headache. Cough stayed but didn’t worry me. Decided I’d go to the doctor.

Day 2: Honestly felt fine, brought her home and chilled playing games all day and finished out some school work. That night my cough got worse but still not that bad. I got a little achy before bed but thought I’d sleep it off
